 MULTIPLE OBJECTS

One class can create many objects.

Example:

class Animal:

    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name

    def show_name(self):
        print(self.name)

animal1 = Animal("Dog")
animal2 = Animal("Cat")

animal1.show_name()
animal2.show_name()

Output:

Dog
Cat

Important:

Class = Animal

Objects = animal1, animal2

Different objects can store different values.

